    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA47-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu ciṟaippuṟamākat tōḻi talaimakaḷukku (G1+2, ET: talaimakaṭku) uraippāḷāyc colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said as one who is speaking to HER while [HE] is behind the hedge.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA47">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            peruṅkaḷi ṟuḻuvai yaṭṭeṉa virumpiṭi</l>
<l>            yuyaṅkupiṇi varuttamō ṭiyaṅkal cellātu</l>
<l>            neytaṟ pācaṭai puraiyu mañcevip</l>
<l>            paitalaṅ kuḻavi taḻīi yoyyeṉa</l>
<l>            varumpuṇ ṇuṟunariṉ varunti vaikuṅ </l>
<l>            kāṉaka nāṭaṟ kituveṉa yāṉatu</l>
<l>            kūṟi ṉevaṉō tōḻi vēṟuṇarn</l>
<l>            taṇaṅkaṟi kaḻaṅkiṟ kōṭṭaṅ kāṭṭi</l>
<l>            veṟiyeṉa vuṇarnta vuḷḷamoṭu maṟiyaṟut</l>
<l>            taṉṉai yayaru murukuniṉ </l>
<l>            poṉṉēr pacalaik kutavā māṟē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>What if I told it, friend,</l>
<l rend="indent2">[with the words] “this [is it]”</l>
<l rend="indent3">to the man from the land inside the forests,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the dark elephant cow, because a tiger has killed the big bull,</l>
<l rend="indent">doesn't get to move(?)<note place="foot">What is the nuance of <term xml:lang="ta">iyaṅkal cellātu</term>? She does not get a movement started?</note> from suffering, a weakening fetter(?),</l>
<l rend="indent">embraces [her] sorrowful pretty calf</l>
<l rend="indent2">with ears pretty like the green leaves of the blue Nelumbo</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] is kept in suffering, 'oy', like those having a heavy wound,</l>
<l>– because Murukaṉ, in whom mother resorts(?),</l>
<l rend="indent3">after she realised [something is] different, the crookedness</l>
<l rend="indent3">of the torment-knowing Molucca beans having been shown,</l>
<l rend="indent3">[and] she had a lamb['s throat] cut, with a mind that realised</l>
<l rend="indent3">“the Veṟi dance [is the remedy]”,</l>
<l>did not contribute to your gold-like pallor?</l>
        </lg>
